s lies at the genesis of the Orion\nNebula Cluster and NGC2023/2024 in Orion B, thus confirming broadly the\nclassical feedback-driven scenario proposed in Elmegreen & Lada (1977). The\nspace motions of the well-known young compact clusters, $\\sigma$ Orionis and\nNGC 1977, are consistent with this scenario. A momentum estimate suggests that\nthe energy of a few to several supernovae is needed to power the coherent 3D\ngas motion we measure in this paper.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 14 Jul 2020 18:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 25 Nov 2020 20:36:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-03-17"}
