{"id":"2007.07607","submitter":"Rainer Klages","authors":"S. Mohsen J. Khadem, Sabine H.L. Klapp, and Rainer Klages","title":"Search efficiency of discrete fractional Brownian motion in a random\n  distribution of targets","comments":"21 pages, 10 figures; final version","journal-ref":"Phys. Rev. Research 3, 023169 (2021)","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevResearch.3.023169","report-no":null,"categories":"cond-mat.stat-mech","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0/","abstract":"  Efficiency of search for randomly distributed targets is a prominent problem\nin many branches of the sciences. For the stochastic process of L\\'evy walks, a\nspecific range of optimal efficiencies was suggested under variation of search\nintrinsic and extrinsic environmental parameters. In this article, we study\nfractional Brownian motion as a search process, which under parameter variation\ngenerates all three basic types of diffusion, from sub- to normal to\nsuperdiffusion. In contrast to L\\'evy walks, fractional Brownian motion defines\na Gaussian stochastic process with power law memory yielding anti-persistent,\nrespectively persistent motion. Computer simulations of search by time-discrete\nfractional Brownian motion in a uniformly random distribution of targets show\nthat maximising search efficiencies sensitively depends on the definition of\nefficiency, the variation of both intrinsic and extrinsic parameters, the\nperception of targets, the type of targets, whether to detect only one or many\nof them, and the choice of boundary conditions. In our simulations we find that\ndifferent search scenarios favour different modes of motion for optimising\nsearch success, defying a universality across all search situations. Some of\nour numerical results are explained by a simple analytical model. Having\ndemonstrated that search by fractional Brownian motion is a truly complex\nprocess, we propose an over-arching conceptual framework based on classifying\ndifferent search scenarios. This approach incorporates search optimisation by\nL\\'evy walks as a special case.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 15 Jul 2020 10:41:38 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 9 Jun 2021 21:47:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-06-11"}
