ower altitude orbits, whilst compliance with\nIADC guidelines for spacecraft post-mission lifetime and deorbit is also\nassisted. Finally, VLEO offers opportunities to exploit novel\natmosphere-breathing electric propulsion systems and aerodynamic attitude and\norbit control methods.\n  However, key challenges associated with our understanding of the lower\nthermosphere, aerodynamic drag, the requirement to provide a meaningful orbital\nlifetime whilst minimising spacecraft mass and complexity, and atomic oxygen\nerosion still require further research. Given the scope for significant\ncommercial, societal, and environmental impact which can be realised with\nhigher performing Earth observation platforms, renewed research efforts to\naddress the challenges associated with VLEO operations are required.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 15 Jul 2020 14:16:34 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 16 Jul 2020 10:10:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-09-15"}
